    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A name-path.</para>
<para>This class represents a name path that points to elements in a configuration document. It allows building paths freely, using individual name elements.</para>
<para>Please note that other than the two different forms in configuration documents, relative and absolute paths use the same text representation when converted from and into text. Relative paths have no name separator prefixed, as this is the case in configuration documents. This lack of difference is due the API treats both forms the same. Addressing a value is always done using relative paths, and the element on which you call the &quot;value&quot; method decides if you start to resolve the path from the root or from a branch in the document.</para>
<para>@tested <computeroutput>NamePathTest</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>NamePathLexerTest</computeroutput> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
